    <statement><p>Anthony hired a face-painter for a birthday party. The painter charged a flat fee of <m>{\$75}</m>, and then charged <m>{\$4.50}</m> per person. 
In the end, Anthony paid a total of <m>{\$129}</m>. How many people used the face-painter<rsq/>s service?</p>
<p><fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/> people used the face-painter<rsq/>s service.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>12</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Let <m>x</m> be the number of people who used the face-painter<rsq/>s service.</p>
<p>The charge for each person was <m>{\$4.50}</m>, so the charge for <m>x</m> people was <m>4.5x</m> dollars. There was also a flat fee of <m>{\$75}</m>.</p>
<p>Now we can write an equation:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 4.5x+75 = 129 }</m></p>
<p>Next, we solve for <m>x</m>:</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
  4.5x +75 \amp = 129 \\
  4.5x +75\mathbf{{} -75} \amp = 129\mathbf{{} -75} \\
  4.5x      \amp = 54 \\
  \frac{4.5x}{4.5} \amp = \frac{54}{4.5} \\
  x   \amp = 12
\end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>So twelve people used the face-painter<rsq/>s service.</p>
</solution>
